      "writtenOn": "2026-07-15T15:15:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "At the Node level, because it\u0027s a merge of field decls, the string here is *always* unquoted. So `x: y: _` and `x: \"y\": _` would both produce a plain string `y` for `name, node :\u003d range x.Fields()` (both individually and together in source).\n\nYou can always get back the original name via `node.Decls().Key()` (in the CL that follows I add `Decl.Label()` because `Key()` may contain only the ast.Node for the field\u0027s value-alias, whereas `Label()` returns the non-alias part",
      "parentUuid": "362944a6_f8c62813",
